cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.RO 

This paper deals with computer vision tasks and proposes a universal convolutional neural network architecture that can handle low-, mid-, and high-level vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also addresses technical challenges related to training a deep architecture with diverse training sets and limited memory, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with region proposal generation and object detection, which could fall under cs.RO (Robotics). Finally, the paper uses neural networks, which could also suggest cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
